<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISPUTE OVER PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am tired of the religious bigots who keep trying to set the rules for what I 
should or should not see in a play at a theater in Costa Mesa. I am referring 
to the controversy surrounding "Sister Mary Ignatius Explains It All for You" 
at the Costa Mesa Civic Playhouse. 
</P>
<P>
I think that the time has come for those religious tyrants, whose religious 
"sensitivities" are offended by anything and everything that does not agree 
100% with their little narrow-minded view of Cosmic Realities, to know that 
there are many ex-churchmen, like myself, who are offended by religious 
censorship and fanaticism. 
</P>
<P>
The zealots, who would like to forbid me and anyone else from seeing this play, 
should realize that they are only making more and more enemies in the artistic 
community. 
</P>
<P>
ALAN ALBERT SNOW 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
