<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
RWANDA; 
</P>
<P>
CAPITAL QUIET AS TROOPS FACE REBELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rwandan capital, Kigali, was reported quiet as French, Belgian and Zairian 
troops arrived to help defend against rebel attack. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, heavy gunfire was reported near the presidential palace, an army 
barracks and the airport. An Air France plane took out 139 people as Westerners 
sought to escape fighting in the small Central African nation. President 
Juvenal Habyarimana said his government had turned the tide against the rebel 
invasion. 
</P>
