<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BODY OF APPARENT MURDER VICTIM FOUND IN RIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a man apparently stabbed and shot to death was found floating in a 
river in the Angeles National Forest north of Azusa Friday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Shortly before noon, two fishermen found the 18- to 22-year-old unidentified 
Latino man's body clad only in brown pants and floating in the West Fork River, 
nearly a mile west of San Gabriel Canyon Road in the national forest, Deputy 
Rich Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim had multiple stab and gunshot wounds in his upper torso, Erickson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide investigators have no suspect and no motive, Erickson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
