<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: OFFICER RECOVERS HIS OWN STOLEN PICKUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A California Highway Patrol officer whose customized pickup truck was stolen 
from his home more than a year ago recovered his cherished vehicle after 
spotting it on a freeway, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Officer Raul Munoz claimed his truck Thursday after he heard the familiar 
rumble of its engine and chased it down in the westbound lanes of the Artesia 
Freeway, CHP Officer Lyle Whitten said. 
</P>
<P>
Munoz was clearing the scene of an accident on the freeway near the San Gabriel 
River Freeway in Cerritos about 1:30 p.m. when he heard the truck's engine and 
looked up to see a 1973 Chevrolet pickup just like his whizzing by, Whitten 
said. He caught up with the driver after a two-mile chase, and noticed details 
he had installed before it was stolen. 
</P>
<P>
The driver had purchased the truck from someone else and was not arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
