Long Beach Municipal Court with 18 counts of sexual assault, kidnaping and 
robbery. Long Beach police were searching for two women they said may have been 
additional victims. Socha, arrested this week in a rented room in Rancho Palos 
Verdes, is the man police believe is the so-called "Messenger of the Lord" 
rapist. He was charged with assaulting four women in Long Beach and San Pedro. 
Police said Socha used a gun to coerce his victims, and an eight-inch, 
double-edged knife to carve upside-down crosses on their backs. Socha's 
arraignment was postponed until Tuesday and he is being held at the Los Angeles 
County Jail hospital without bail, Deputy Dist. Atty. Jim Cosper said. LARRY 
