<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESIGNATION OVER SENTENCING LAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tough new sentencing guidelines aren't dehumanizing; exactly the opposite, 
they hold some promise that criminals pay dearly with hard time behind bars, 
providing a small measure of hope the rest of us might live a more human (read: 
secure) existence. 
</P>
<P>
I believe there are many like myself who hope President Bush will replace Judge 
Irving with a fair-minded, energetic judge who will have no problem with tough 
sentencing, with luck, one who will also have "fun" doing so. 
</P>
<P>
JEFF GHOLSON 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
