<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
GOP CANDIDATES TO ATTEND PARTY RALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Republican candidates for county and state offices will speak at a rally in 
Oxnard on Sunday to raise money for the party's Ventura County headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers expect to attract about 300 people in hopes of raising at least 
$7,500 for its main party headquarters in Camarillo and this year's campaign 
base in Oxnard, spokeswoman Jean Dewey said. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets cost $25 for the Western-style meal at the McGrath Ranch, 5011 W. 
Gonzales Road. 
</P>
<P>
The annual rally, sponsored by the Ventura County Republican Party Central 
Committee, does not aim to promote individual candidates, although several will 
speak at the event between 1 and 5 p.m., Dewey said. 
</P>
<P>
Representatives Elton Gallegly (R-Simi Valley) and Robert J. Lagomarsino 
(R-Ventura), Assemblywoman Cathie Wright (R-Simi Valley) and Assemblyman Tom 
McClintock (R-Thousand Oaks) will be among those reporting on recent 
legislation. KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
