<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: WOMAN FOUND TO HAVE BEEN STRANGLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 37-year-old woman whose nude body was found in a Westlake Village condominium 
was strangled, Deputy Coroner Craig Stevens reported Friday after an autopsy. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura County sheriff's investigators found Ellen Cleary's body Thursday 
afternoon in a bathtub in a small amount of water, Lt. Joe Harwell said. 
</P>
<P>
Officials do not know whether she was taking a bath or was placed there by the 
killer. 
</P>
<P>
Timothy Velasco, 22, of Van Nuys told Los Angeles police that he killed his 
girlfriend and gave them details that led sheriff's deputies to Cleary's 
condominium in the 1100 block of Bright Glen Circle, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Despite Velasco's admission to the slaying, investigators have failed to find a 
motive. 
</P>
<P>
"We feel confident we know who perpetrated the crime. But why? It's not an easy 
question to answer," Harwell said. 
</P>
<P>
Velasco told authorities that he had known Cleary for three years and that she 
was his girlfriend, Harwell said. 
</P>
<P>
Bail was set at $1 million. PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
