<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
SESSIONS PLANNED ON BALLOT PROPOSITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The League of Women Voters of Ventura County has scheduled presentations this 
month to help voters confused by any of the 18 propositions on the November 
ballot. 
</P>
<P>
"The pros and cons listed on the ballot are often written by legal people or 
legislative analysts," said Roma Armbrust, the league's county president. "Our 
speakers put the arguments in more easily understandable terms, and the public 
has an opportunity to ask questions." 
</P>
<P>
The first of the six pro-and-con sessions, which -- like the league's upcoming 
candidate forums -- are free to the public, is scheduled at the American Legion 
Hall in Ventura on Thursday at 12:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Other programs are scheduled at the Thousand Oaks Library, Oct. 22 at 7 p.m.; 
the Ojai Presbyterian Church, Oct. 23 at 9:30 a.m.; the United Methodist Church 
in Santa Paula, Oct. 24 at 7 p.m.; Ventura City Hall, Oct. 25 at 7:30 p.m.; and 
the Simi Valley Library, Oct. 26 at 7 p.m. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
