<P>
NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BARTLETT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Paula 17, Santa Ynez 10 -- Fullback Eddie Rabago scored on a three-yard 
run for the deciding score with 19 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Rabago's run capped a seven-play, 65-yard drive that consumed two minutes for 
Santa Paula (3-2). The winning drive was keyed by Ben Fausset's 50-yard pass to 
Ray Rodriguez. Fausset completed 17 of 40 passes for 296 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Paula's Dustin Magdaleno, who caught five passes for 54 yards and a 
touchdown, has 122 career catches to break the Ventura County reception record 
(118) set by Matt Young of Santa Clara. MIKE BARTLETT 
</P>
</TEXT>
