SOUTHERN SECTION ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
IN OTHER MARMONTE LEAGUE GAMES: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royal 10, Newbury Park 0 -- Defensive back Tim Ross forced a fumble after 
catching Newbury Park's Leodes Van Buren from behind on a 73-yard pass play and 
teammate Matt Tomaszewski recovered with 7:34 left to preserve the win at 
Moorpark College. 
</P>
<P>
Tomaszewski, a senior linebacker, hadn't practiced most of the week because of 
the death of his mother. 
</P>
<P>
He led an inspired Royal defense, which limited Newbury Park (1-4, 0-2) to 13 
yards rushing and 73 yards passing, all of which came on one play. 
</P>
<P>
Highlander quarterback Ryan Fien connected on a 10-yard scoring strike to Tony 
Liming on fourth down with 2:11 to play in the third quarter. Steve Prchal's 
conversion completed the scoring. Prchal booted a 40-yard field goal in the 
first quarter to give Royal (5-0, 2-0) a 3-0 lead at the half. 
</P>
<P>
Fien finished with 114 yards, completing 13 of 28 passes with one touchdown and 
one interception. GREG MEADE 
</P>
</TEXT>
