</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Savings Bond Sales Hits Three-Year High: The Treasury said the sale of U.S. 
savings bonds hit a three-year high of $7.77 billion in the year ending Sept. 
30. 
</P>
<P>
Boosting the total were sales of $544 million in September, a 3% advance over a 
year ago. At the same time, redemptions in fiscal 1990 totaled $7.54 billion, a 
1% drop from 1989. The value of savings bonds held by Americans rose 7% during 
the year, finishing at an all-time record $123.9 billion, up from $115.7 
billion in 1989. 
