</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kluge Boosts Stake in Orion: Struggling Orion Pictures received a boost as 
majority shareholder Metromedia Co., controlled by billionaire John Kluge, 
increased its stake to 80% from 70%. 
</P>
<P>
Orion, battered by a string of duds at the box office, said Metromedia had 
exercised warrants to buy slightly more than 4.3 million shares of common stock 
at $6 a share. The transaction will give Orion, which lost $2.5 million on 
revenue of $110 million in its first quarter, a $25-million cash infusion. 
Orion's stock rose 37.5 cents to $9.875 a share on the NYSE. 
