<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUP PLOT REPORTEDLY UNCOVERED IN GUYANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GEORGETOWN, Guyana 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police on Friday said they uncovered a possible coup plot in Guyana and 
arrested 10 people, including a former army officer and a police official. 
</P>
<P>
Few details were available about the alleged plot, which would be the second 
such conspiracy in less than 18 months in Guyana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
