<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
CRASH KILLS WOMAN AFTER BIRTHDAY PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LUCY CHABOT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 28-year-old Anaheim woman who had just celebrated her birthday with friends 
died in an early morning car crash Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Lori Hrifko spent Thursday evening celebrating with friends at a restaurant in 
Newport Beach and was driving her 1985 Nissan 300 SX, loaded with presents and 
flowers, home when she lost control and hit a tree at about 12:15 a.m., police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was on the northbound San Diego Freeway off-ramp at Brookhurst Street 
when her car veered to the left, said California Highway Patrol Officer Lyle 
Whitten. 
</P>
<P>
When she tried to straighten the car out, she overcompensated and ran off the 
right side, hitting a tree, Whitten said. 
</P>
<P>
Police found a broken, unlit cigarette on the seat of the car and believe 
Hrifko may have been distracted trying to light it when she veered off the 
off-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
"She was going much too fast in order to take that ramp safely," Whitten said, 
estimating her speed at 55 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
"It looks like something distracted her attention. She may have been reaching 
for a match when she hit the curb, then just overcompensated to the right. 
There was no other visible reason why she couldn't have stayed in control," 
Whitten said. LUCY CHABOT 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100690-0142 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 288532 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 6, 1990, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
