<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
AGENCIES REQUEST BIDS FOR 2 TOLLWAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFFREY A. PERLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange County's toll road agencies solicited bids Friday from four firms 
competing for contracts to design and build two county tollways. 
</P>
<P>
The Transportation Corridor Agencies, which are overseeing the projects, sent 
the bid forms to a joint venture of Penni Corp. and Guy F. Atkinson Co., 
Ohbayashi Corp., California Corridor Construction (a consortium of Kiewit 
Pacific Co., Granite Construction Co. and De Leuw Cather &amp; Co.), and 
Morrison Knudsen Corp. The bids will involve the San Joaquin Hills and Eastern 
tollways, which are estimated to cost more than $1.3 billion combined. 
</P>
<P>
The San Joaquin Hills tollway is an extension of California 73 from Newport 
Beach through the coastal hills to Interstate 5 near San Juan Capistrano. The 
Eastern tollway is a new route from the Riverside Freeway near Weir Canyon 
through the mountains to the Santa Ana Freeway in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The San Joaquin Hills project is scheduled to be built first, with selection of 
a firm for construction due in February. JEFFREY A. PERLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
