<P>
WESTMINSTER MAN SHOT BY ATTACKER OUTSIDE HIS HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LUCY CHABOT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was shot and slightly wounded Friday night by one of two men who accosted 
the victim and his wife while they were parking their car at home. 
</P>
<P>
Sinh Ngoc Vu, 41, was shot once in the right knee shortly after 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The two assailants then fled without demanding or taking any property, Police 
Lt. Andrew Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
Vu and his wife were driving their car into their garage when the two men 
approached them and demanded that Vu get out of the car. When he didn't respond 
immediately, Hall said, one of the men opened the car door and shot him in the 
knee. 
</P>
<P>
Hall said Vu heard one man say, "Kill him," as the two fled. They drove off in 
a white 1986 Honda Civic with a blue stripe. 
</P>
<P>
Vu was taken to Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center, where he 
was treated and released. His wife, who was not identified, was not harmed, 
Hall said. LUCY CHABOT 
</P>
</TEXT>
