<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE WINS ON LATE FIELD GOAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Garden Grove High School's Adrian Ioja kicked a 26-yard field goal with 11 
seconds left Friday to give the Argonauts a 6-3 victory over Santiago in a 
Garden Grove League game. 
</P>
<P>
Seven minutes after Santiago's Dan Agramont kicked a 32-yard field goal at the 
start of the second quarter, Ioja tied the game with a 36-yarder of his own. 
</P>
<P>
Neither team was able to score again until the fourth quarter. Garden Grove 
quarterback Simon Fuentes (three of seven for 56 yards) marched the Argonauts 
(2-3 overall, 1-1 in league) for four first downs and got them within 
field-goal range, but Ioja missed a 38-yarder. 
</P>
<P>
But neither Fuentes nor Ioja was through. With less than a minute left in the 
game, Fuentes hit wide receiver Jason Baca with a 36-yard pass, and Santiago 
(1-4, 1-1)was called for a face-mask penalty. Three plays later, Ioja redeemed 
himself with the game-winner. 
</P>
<P>
"Our defense finally showed up for a ballgame," said Buenafe. 
</P>
<P>
The Garden Grove defense held quarterback Mike Carrasco to five completions in 
15 attempts for 57 yards and an interception and minus-26 yards rushing, 
Santiago carried for just 11 yards.HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
