<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAVANNA BLOCKS A FIELD GOAL, SALVAGES TIE WITH LAGUNA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MISSION VIEJO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Savanna High School blocked a 25-yard field goal attempt by Laguna Hills' Marc 
Brodbeck with seven seconds remaining in the game to preserve a 7-7 tie Friday 
night at Mission Viejo High School. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels' (3-1-1) defensive front penetrated the Hawks' offensive line and 
several players smothered Brodbeck's low kick. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills (3-1-1) moved the ball into field goal position after Mark 
Bochenek recovered a fumble by Savanna's Randall Morgan at the Rebel 44-yard 
line with 1:52 left. Marwan Saba gained 14 yards in two running plays, and then 
quarterback Casey Sullivan hit tight end Kirk Brown for a 19-yard gain to the 
Savanna 10 with 16 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
An off-tackle run by Saba moved the ball into the middle of the field at the 
eight, but the blocked kick ended Laguna Hills' would-be winning drive. 
</P>
<P>
Savanna took a 7-0 lead in the first quarter on Jeff Ragos' one-yard touchdown 
run. Ragos' score capped a 34-yard drive that was set up by Hien Nguyen's 
19-yard punt return. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills tied the score in the third quarter. Savanna fumbled away the ball 
at its 23-yard line. Saba finished the eight-play drive with a one-yard 
touchdown run with 4:21 left in the quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
