<HEADLINE>
<P>
LUEVANOS' THREE TOUCHDOWN PASSES LEAD BREA TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BREA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Jason Luevanos threw for three touchdowns and rushed for another to 
lead Brea-Olinda High School to a 33-17 victory over El Dorado Friday night in 
a nonleague football game at Brea. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Irvin accounted for two touchdowns in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
His one-yard run with 7:08 left gave Brea (3-2) a 26-10 lead. He also caught a 
four-yard scoring pass from Luevanos with 1:22 left for the final score. 
</P>
<P>
After El Dorado (1-4) took a 3-0 lead in the first quarter on a 26-yard field 
goal by Mike Roth, Brea took a 7-3 lead as Luevanos escaped a pass rush and 
raced 24 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado took a 10-7 lead on a one-yard scoring run by Eric Ayala with almost 
seven minutes left in the half on fourth and goal. 
</P>
<P>
Brea regained the lead for good with 1:30 left in the half after Lance Gasporra 
recovered an El Dorado fumble at the Golden Hawk 29. Three plays later, 
Luevanos completed a three-yard touchdown pass to Jamie Baraglia. Brea led, 
13-10, after the extra-point try was missed. 
</P>
<P>
Neither team scored in the third quarter, but with 9:16 left in the game, 
Luevanos completed a five-yard touchdown to Mike Ryan and Brea led, 20-10. DALE 
RUHE 
</P>
</TEXT>
