<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAILORS TOP ESTANCIA WITH BIG FIRST HALF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior quarterback Steve Walker completed 10 of 17 passes for 132 yards and two 
touchdowns to lead Newport Harbor High School to a 31-7 victory over Estancia 
Friday night at Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
Marc Tagliaferri, a 6-foot-3, 180-pound running back, added 105 yards and a 
touchdown in 13 carries for the Sailors (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor broke the game open with 2:42 left in the first half when Walker 
hit senior tight end George Greenwalt with a 25-yard touchdown pass. Josh 
Klein's extra point made it 14-7 Newport Harbor. On the next series, junior 
linebacker Darin Mangnall recovered a fumble at the Estancia 17-yard line. Two 
plays later, Walker and junior wide receiver Branon Coluccio teamed on a 
four-yard touchdown pass with 1:26 left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
Klein added a 44-yard field goal as time ran out in the half to give Newport 
Harbor a 24-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia (1-4) scored its only touchdown with 6:41 left in the half on a 
third-and-eight at the Newport Harbor 22-yard line. Senior running back David 
Hong caught a pass from sophomore quarterback Matt Johner at the Eagle 35, 
broke two tackles and ran 78 yards for the touchdown. LEN HALL 
</P>
