<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS HOLDS OFF MAGNOLIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cypress High School scored three times in the fourth quarter and held off 
Magnolia's rally to post a 28-19 nonleague victory Friday at Handel Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Kakalia's 23-yard interception return with 1:10 to play sealed the victory 
after Magnolia's Ariel Couvetier made the score 21-19 on a 98-yard kickoff 
return with five minutes to play. 
</P>
<P>
A 19-yard pass from Gabe Garcia to Yousef Seeman and a 29-yard run by Bryan 
Dawson accounted for Cypress' other second-half scores. 
</P>
<P>
Magnolia (1-4) scored on a 60-yard fumble return by John Garcia with 3:08 to 
play in the third quarter for the Sentinels' first touchdown in four games. 
Early in the fourth quarter, Magnolia took a 12-7 lead on a one-yard run by 
Couvetier set up by a Cypress fumble. But the Centurions came right back on a 
six-play, 80-yard drive capped by Seeman's touchdown reception with 10:25 to 
play. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress (2-3) had a strong defensive effort that held Magnolia to 115 total 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
After a scoreless first half, Joe Groover opened the scoring with a six-yard 
pass from Garcia that capped a 10-play, 61-yard drive with 5:52 left in the 
third quarter. SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
