<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Grand Prize in the Orange County American Institute of Architects' 
Invitational Sandcastle Competition, held Sunday in Corona del Mar, has gone to 
Dougherty &amp; Dougherty of Newport Beach for "Cinderella's Castle." In the 
sandcastle category, Wimberly, Allison, Tong &amp; Goo of Newport Beach won 
first place for "Castle of the Gods" (which also won the People's Choice 
award). 
</P>
<P>
Dougherty &amp; Dougherty took second place, and Dan L. Rowland &amp; 
Associates of Anaheim placed third. In the sand sculpture category, WRC 
Associates of Newport Beach took first prize. Second prize went to "Man vs. 
Environment," a depiction of the Exxon Valdez oil spill by CYP Inc. of Irvine. 
Florian Martinez Associates of Tustin placed third for an image of a man 
floating in an inner tube. Criteria for selection included originality, level 
of difficulty and use of site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
