<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crime figures -- State Department of Justice crime figures in a chart that 
appeared Friday in The Times were incorrectly transcribed in three cases. 
</P>
<P>
In Anaheim, there were 20,057 major crimes reported overall and 5,496 were 
solved, a rate of 27%. In Fresno, 8,095 burglaries were reported and 1,133 were 
solved -- a rate of 14%. In San Francisco, 380 cases were reported and 204 were 
solved -- 54%. The changes do not alter Long Beach's rate of solving major 
crimes -- 14%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
